The paper focuses on modeling manipulation tasks for robots and humans using a combination of vision and language models, which is a common theme in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also heavily relies on computer vision techniques to process real-world camera streams (cs.CV). The proposed scheme involves generating visual attentions and an evolving knowledge graph, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also involves natural language processing techniques to work with the ontology system (cs.CL).
